{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"965a4c9e-a059-4524-927e-f498d50817d1","content":"The directory appears to be empty — there's no workflow file to inspect. No worries, here's a general guide for switching from `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` to **NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC)**:\n\n---\n\n### What to change\n\n**1. NuGet.org side — register your repo**\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → [your package] → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a new GitHub Actions policy: set your **repository owner**, **repo name**, and optionally an **environment** or **branch** filter.\n\n**2. Workflow: add `id-token` permission**\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # request OIDC token\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**3. Workflow: replace the `dotnet nuget push` step**\n\nBefore (API key):\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -k ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nAfter (OIDC):\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json --api-key az\n  env:\n    NUGET_TOKEN: ${{ steps.nuget-auth.outputs.token }}\n```\n\nOr, more commonly with the **`dotnet nuget push` trusted-publishers flow**:\n```yaml\n- name: Push to NuGet (OIDC)\n  run: |\n    dotnet nuget add source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json \\\n      --name nuget.org \\\n      --username \"az\" \\\n      --password \"${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\" \\\n      --store-password-in-clear-text\n    dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source nuget.org\n```\n\n> **Note:** The exact push mechanism depends on your `dotnet` SDK version. With SDK 9+ and NuGet 6.13+, you can use the native OIDC support:\n\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json --api-key OIDC\n```\n\n**4. Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret** from your repo settings once OIDC is working.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of changes\n\n| Area | Old | New |\n|---|---|---|\n| Auth method | `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC token via `id-token: write` |\n| NuGet.org config | API key | Trusted publisher policy |\n| Push command | `-k ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` | `--api-key OIDC` (SDK 9+) |\n| Secret management | Must rotate key | No secret needed |\n\nIf you share your workflow file I can make the exact edits for you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"41538cbf-7c27-4016-bdad-e72542e2f67e","outputTokens":710},"id":"e00eb9e5-7b7e-486a-9c37-327713eea03f","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:38:40.204Z","parentId":"68dcde40-b6f6-46f9-8f78-7ddeb14e6dd6"}
